### Step 1: `src/schemas/registry.ts` — Discriminated Union Registry Schema

Replace the single flat `RegistryEntrySchema` with three discriminated member schemas joined by `z.discriminatedUnion`. Maintain backward compatibility for old `skill-dir` entries that may have been written without the `method` field defaulting.

```typescript
// New schema structure (pseudocode — not actual file write)

const SkillDirRegistryEntrySchema = z.object({
  kind: z.literal("skill-dir"),
  source: z.string(),
  skill: z.string(),
  agent: AgentIdSchema,
  method: z.enum(["symlink", "copy"]).optional(),
  deployed: z.string(),
});

const FileWriteRegistryEntrySchema = z.object({
  kind: z.literal("file-write"),
  source: z.string(),
  skill: z.string(),
  agent: AgentIdSchema,
  deployed: z.string(),
});

const ConfigPatchRegistryEntrySchema = z.object({
  kind: z.literal("config-patch"),
  patch: z.record(z.string(), z.unknown()),   // the patch that was applied
  undoPatch: z.record(z.string(), z.unknown()), // original values (null = key was absent)
  skill: z.string(),
  agent: AgentIdSchema,
  deployed: z.string(),
});

export const RegistryEntrySchema = z.discriminatedUnion("kind", [
  SkillDirRegistryEntrySchema,
  FileWriteRegistryEntrySchema,
  ConfigPatchRegistryEntrySchema,
]);

export const RegistrySchema = z.object({
  version: z.literal(1),
  deployments: z.record(z.string(), RegistryEntrySchema),
});

export type SkillDirRegistryEntry = z.infer<typeof SkillDirRegistryEntrySchema>;
export type FileWriteRegistryEntry = z.infer<typeof FileWriteRegistryEntrySchema>;
export type ConfigPatchRegistryEntry = z.infer<typeof ConfigPatchRegistryEntrySchema>;
export type RegistryEntry = z.infer<typeof RegistryEntrySchema>;
export type Registry = z.infer<typeof RegistrySchema>;
```

**Backward compatibility note**: The existing `skill-dir` flat schema writes `{ kind, source, skill, agent, method?, deployed }`. The new `SkillDirRegistryEntrySchema` is structurally identical to the old flat schema for `skill-dir` entries, so old files parse correctly under the new discriminated union without a migration step. The old schema had `source: z.string()` as required for all kinds — with the union, `source` is only required on `skill-dir` and `file-write`, never on `config-patch`, which is the structural fix needed.

**What changes in this file**:
- Remove the old flat `RegistryEntrySchema`
- Add the three kind-specific schemas above
- Export the new union as `RegistryEntrySchema` (same export name, same `RegistryEntry` type alias — callers in `ownership.ts` use these names and will pick up the narrowed union automatically)
- Export the three concrete entry types individually so `ownership.ts` and `deploy.ts` can narrow by kind

