   - logger.detail(`write-file: ${action.source} -> ${action.target}`)
   - Push PlannedChange{ verb: "write-file", ... } into planned
   - Return { error: null }
3. await mkdir(path.dirname(action.target), { recursive: true })
4. Check if target exists (lstat):
   - If it does, call verifyDeployment with { kind: "file-write", source, skill, agent }
   - If not managed, throw "Target exists but not managed by inception-engine"
5. await copyFile(action.source, action.target)   // node:fs/promises copyFile
6. await registerDeployment(home, action.target, {
     kind: "file-write",
     source: action.source,
     skill: action.skill,
     agent: action.agent,
   })
7. logger.ok(label)
```

